  "prompt": "In watchos menu is not opened by force touching on interface controller why?",
  "response": "The behavior of Force Touch has changed across various Apple devices and watchOS versions over time, and starting from watchOS 7, Apple has removed Force Touch from the interface. The company decided to eliminate Force Touch in favor of long-press interactions, which are simpler for users and also useful for those who faced difficulty using Force Touch gestures.\n\nAs a result, on watchOS versions post-watchOS 7, Force Touch no longer opens menus or performs actions that it used to. Instead, you need to follow the new interaction models such as long-pressing or tapping on specific interface elements to access context menus or additional options. This change streamlines the user interaction model and aligns it with other Apple devices, providing a more consistent user experience across the ecosystem.\n\nIf you're developing or using watchOS apps, make sure to update or adapt the interface controllers accordingly to align with the new interaction patterns introduced by Apple.",
